<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-098-580  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 098 580.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Canadian Datasystems  Dec 1989 v20 n12 p17(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Fibre-optic transmission is now competitive with other systems,and on bits-per-buck basis is clearly ahead.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Kaye, Ivor.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Fiber optical transmission systems will, in time, become thestandard for most premises.andP;  Three factors converge to promotefiber optics: cost reductions, introduction of standards such asFiber Distributed Data interface (FDDI), and growth in bandwidthrequirements for data communications applications.andP;  A standardFDDI fiber circuit runs at 100M bps and handles multiple Ethernetsoperating at 10M bps per channel, multiple token rings at 16M bps,video channels at full or compressed rate, with plenty of capacityremaining for multiple T1 ISDN channels.andP;  Impediments to afull-scale shift to fiber options include lack of PBX-basedsystems with direct interface, and user understanding of thetechnology.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Fiber OpticsForecastingTrendsMarketMarket Analysis.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>